<apex:pageBlockSection title="Understanding SMS Automation using workflow" onclick="collapseSection('secondSection');" />
<div id="secondSection" style="display:block;">
<b>It automates SMS Actions using workflow rules based on your organization's processes.</b><br/><br/>
<ol type="1">
<li>SMS Alerts - Send an SMS to one or more recipients you specify.</li><br/>
<li>SMS Campaigns - Trigger Mass SMSes to particular Campaign's members.</li><br/>
<li>Auto SMS Replies - Send SMS for to reply on email/sms queries.</li>
</ol> 
</div>
<apex:pageBlockSection title="Dependencies">
<b>This package has below dependencies : </b><br/><br/>
<ol type="1">
<li>Salesforce Enterprise or Unlimited editions</li><br/>
<li>SMS Magic Interact version 1.30 and above</li><br/>
<li>SMS Credits (To buy credits <a href="http://screen-magic.com/salesforce/shoppingCart.html">click here</a>)</li>
</ol>
</apex:pageBlockSection>
<apex:pageBlockSection title="Examples" onclick="collapseSection('examplesSection');" />
<div id="examplesSection" style="display:block;">
<b>How to configuration Action for Contact</b><br/><br/>
Follow steps below to configure Action :
<ol type="1">
<li>Create Workflow Rule for Contact.</li><br/>
<li>Create XML Configuration for Contact.</li><br/>
<li>Copy XML Configuration Id.</li><br/>
<li>In workflow Action, choose the option to Create Task.</li> <br/>
<li>Enter any name as the subject.</li><br/>
<li>Paste Configuration id,copied in step 3 in comments under Workflow Task Description section.</li><br/>
<li>Activate Workflow Rule.</li><br/>
</ol>

<b>How to configuration Action for Campaign:</b><br/><br/>
<ol type="1">
<li>Create Workflow Rule for Campaign.</li><br/>
<li>Create XML Configuration for Campaign.</li><br/>
<li>Copy XML Configuration Id.</li><br/>
<li>In workflow Action, choose the option to Create Task.</li><br/>
<li>Enter any name as the subject.</li><br/>
<li>Paste Configuration id,copied in step 3 in comments under Workflow Task Description section.</li><br/>
<li>Activate Workflow Rule.</li><br/>
</ol>
</div>


<apex:pageBlockSection title="Limitations" onclick="collapseSection('limitationsBlock');" />
<div id="limitationsBlock" style="display:block;">
<ul type="disc">
<li>Any Object not relatable to tasks is not supported i.e. Campaign member object is not supported.</li><br/>
<li>Event object is partially supported.</li><br/>
<li>SMS to object record's owner is not supported.</li>
</ul>
</div>
